      "id": 740,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:23",
      "content": "Fix the right panel not defaulting to Tasks on load in `public/app.js`.\n\nThe variable `rightPanelTab` is set to `'tasks'` but `switchRightTab` is never called on initialization, so the DOM keeps Events visible and Tasks hidden.\n\nFind the block that sets up the right panel tab listeners (around line 432-433):\n```\n  tabEvents.addEventListener('click', () => switchRightTab('events'));\n  tabTasks.addEventListener('click', () => switchRightTab('tasks'));\n```\n\nAdd one line immediately after both listeners:\n```\n  switchRightTab('tasks');   // initialize to default\n```\n\nThat's the only change needed. Commit: `Fix: call switchRightTab on load to initialize Tasks as default panel`\n\nReport DONE to cec50b17:0.",
